-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: rewrite digest and attention as the prioritized action queue","description":"Rewrite digest and attention so they form the heart of the ongoing operator loop rather than acting like separate vaguely-related summaries. This task exists because ntm's strongest agent-native idea is the attention feed, and the redesign should put that at the center.","design":"Digest should answer what changed since a cursor in grouped, replay-safe form, including correlated actuation outcomes, operator attention-state changes, and intentional resurfacing of previously cooled-down or snoozed issues. Attention should answer what deserves action now, with reason codes, freshness, severity, stable resource references, request or outcome correlation handles where relevant, structured next_actions or equivalent remediation descriptors, compact evidence summaries or explanation handles, explicit aggregation or suppression markers when items represent rolled-up churn rather than raw event volume, and clear indicators when an item is pinned, snoozed, acknowledged, muted, or manually escalated. The two surfaces should feel like adjacent views over the same durable state rather than unrelated features, and they should bridge cleanly into inspect and diagnostics flows when an operator needs to understand why an item is present or absent. This task is where ntm steals the derived-actionability lesson from vibe_cockpit without adopting its fleet or analytics posture.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when digest and attention are coherent, prioritized, cursor-aware surfaces that help an agent tend the system over time instead of repeatedly rescanning the entire world, while still supporting safe retries, verified outcomes, durable operator control, and a concise signal-to-noise ratio.","notes":"If agents still need to reconstruct the next action from raw dumps, the redesign has missed its main ergonomic payoff.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:17.499375794Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:22.493690943Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:31.860408763Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:48.280017075Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:58.558445530Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:23.095867952Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:34.463848955Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:25.674213998Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:49.170632351Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:03.333815090Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:31.912454353Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:03.868060207Z","created_by":"ubuntu"