 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: rationalize targeted inspect surfaces for session and agent drill-down","description":"Rationalize the drill-down surfaces used after bootstrap and triage for session and agent inspection. This task exists because operators need to inspect panes, agents, output, activity, context, and process state in detail, but that detail should project from the shared model instead of recreating command sprawl.","design":"The work should decide which session and agent inspect views remain distinct commands or modes, how they key into sessions, agents, and panes, how invalid or stale lookup requests are reported with machine-actionable follow-up guidance, and how they expose detail that is too verbose for snapshot, status, or attention. It should also make explicit how output, activity, context, and process detail is presented without leaking raw tmux mechanics back into the surface contract, and where these views deliberately hand off to the shared diagnostics flow when deeper why, evidence, truncation, or replay context is needed.\n\nThe goal is disciplined drill-down for session and agent state, not a generic debug dump.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when session and agent inspect surfaces are coherently defined and backed by the shared runtime projection with stable keys, detail semantics, and user-facing purpose.","notes":"A useful heuristic: a session or agent inspect surface should answer a focused follow-up question raised by snapshot or attention, not replace them.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:18.455554982Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:32.748220036Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["inspect","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:59.118868718Z","created_by":